I'm not sure I fully get the explanation from your EDIT.  If you had a single scope resolution operator ::, classes and namespaces should share the same hash and lookup. A class is, fundamentally, a namespace.<p>namespace foo;
function bar(){echo "func\n";}<p>class foo{
static function bar(){echo "func\n";}
}<p>Should be equivalent as far as invoking them is concerned.
